-- Colombian Stock Movers: Cementos Argos Drops; Grupo Sura Gains
-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 2012-01-20T16:50:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-20/colombian-stock-movers-cementos-argos-drops-grupo-sura-gains.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:49 a.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  rose 0.1 percent to 13,484.69, while the
Colcap Index fell 0.1 percent to 1,604.34.  Cementos Argos SA (CEMARGOS)  ,  Colombia ’s biggest cement
maker, dropped 0.9 percent to 10,700 pesos. The company is
considering selling bonds and short-term notes in the domestic
market, according to a regulatory filing yesterday.  The company’s total debt outstanding was 3.1 trillion pesos
($1.7 billion) as of Sept. 30, according to data compiled by
Bloomberg.  Grupo de Inversiones Suramericana SA  (GRUPOSUR CB), the
parent company of Colombia’s biggest bank, rose 1.3 percent to
31,300 pesos. The company said it will begin the regulatory
process to merge operations of its Colombian pension fund,
Proteccion SA, and ING Administradora de Pensiones y Cesantias
SA, according to a regulatory filing late yesterday.  The group, in the same filing, also denied reports that it
is planning to create a brokerage business.  To contact the reporter on this story:
